Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.21,0:00:05.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After following the instruction of\Na strange letter Uncle received...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.42,0:00:08.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We ended up visiting Koura Inn in Gunma prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.75,0:00:14.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,According to two people we met along the way,\NTokubi Rokurou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Araiwa Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.47,0:00:16.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Eleven years ago, in the river near the inn..
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.43,0:00:22.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,An elementary school student named Numayama\NTatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} got swept away by a flood and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this have been the "murder" mentioned in the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.57,0:00:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the man that kicked over the riverside\Ngrave made by Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The father, Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was also strange in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.58,0:00:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next morning, Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was found in the attic...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drowned in the water from the reservoir\Nwhere Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the work of the kappa that\NRan claimed to have seen last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.51,0:00:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.14,0:00:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone How I long for you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.93,0:01:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone Though I already know
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.64,0:01:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you'll someday come back to say your regrets —\hyeah stay with me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.24,0:01:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.96,0:01:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.59,0:01:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instpector Yamamura of the Gunma police...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.40,0:01:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will be revealing the sad truth behind the kappa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.66,0:01:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.17,0:01:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the thrilling one-scene in a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.05,0:01:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My heart has been penetrated through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.05,0:01:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel my love has gone away like a dream, ta-la-ta • • baby I need you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.18,0:01:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When summer comes, I somehow long for the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.52,0:01:58.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should've already forgotten, but my heart, Baby, just want to be there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.16,0:02:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone How I long for you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.08,0:02:08.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone Though I already know
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That it really is impossible to return to that summer day from here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.18,0:02:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone It'd be best if I laughed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.01,0:02:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone That fool of a guy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.77,0:02:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someday he'll come back to say his regrets —\hyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.07,0:02:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer time gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan is brought to you by P&G and these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:56.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,THE DREAM THE KAPPA SAW
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:56.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.68,0:03:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the reportage writer just now was telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.81,0:03:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor-in-charge confirmed that they were conversing\Nback and forth for over an hour without any pauses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he couldn't have drowned someone while making the call,huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.70,0:03:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.20,0:03:15.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've finished getting all of the inn employee's alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.25,0:03:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of crime, it seems everyone was preparing breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.70,0:03:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say that one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.90,0:03:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.46,0:03:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.71,0:03:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inn employee's alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.25,0:03:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.95,0:03:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.75,0:03:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Inspector Yamamura"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.55,0:03:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.68,0:03:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you have something to report to Inspector Yamamura?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.80,0:03:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.76,0:03:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think this hack was promoted to inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, we have confirmed that the water\Nin question is a match to the reservoir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.44,0:03:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, was there anyone who snuck out of this inn last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:04:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who went out last night\Nwas your group and Nohira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.74,0:04:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted to take pictures of the scenery\Naround here, and he left earlier than you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.25,0:04:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he came back dripping wet after\Nyou guys did, according to the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.09,0:04:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, why did you guys leave the inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.92,0:04:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran said she dropped her cell phone\Nby the river, so we went to Iook for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.05,0:04:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, there it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.26,0:04:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A real kappa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.60,0:04:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again with the kappa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I swear it was really there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.81,0:04:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right next to where I dropped my phone,\Nit was standing in the middle of the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.69,0:04:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you didn't try to take any pictures as evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you have your phone in your hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was too scared to do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, why don't I try to make a picture of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:47.66,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tokubi Rokurou (42)\NPainter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.58,0:04:47.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind me drawing it in\Nmy soaked and distorted sketchbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.09,0:04:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the beak was bigger than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.67,0:04:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About this size?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.97,0:04:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.30,0:05:04.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For someone to have been drowned in a water\Nbucket, at least one liter of water would be reguired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.60,0:05:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why were we unable to locate the\Ncontainer used to transport the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s color ink bottles were full, and\Nhe's actually painting with them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.77,0:05:17.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Araiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s plastic bottle had its seal broken,\Nbut it still had half of its oolong tea remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.36,0:05:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His water pillow also didn't have any water inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspicion thus falls on Nohira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for\Nhaving so many film canisters, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has an alibi because he was talking on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.67,0:05:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To begin with, the fact that Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was\Nonly wearing his swim shorts strikes me as odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.63,0:05:39.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he were going cold-weather\Nswimming, would he wear his shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.22,0:05:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, that shoe...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were multiple green stains on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.48,0:05:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really see this kind of thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.86,0:05:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was this exact scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, let me see it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you're not going to say that the kappa is the culprit, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a kappa...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.34,0:06:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is obviously...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An alien!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.89,0:06:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alien!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.18,0:06:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.18,0:06:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this era where space travel is possible, it wouldn't be odd for\Nan extraterrestrial to have come from a distant planet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.31,0:06:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, why don't you tell us where\Nthe spaceship is that it came on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.15,0:06:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.44,0:06:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate their scientific prowess!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.24,0:06:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their spaceship may appear to be this small...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.74,0:06:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But thousands of shrunken extraterrestrials\Ncan tightly fill it for them to travel here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.37,0:06:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.79,0:06:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.46,0:06:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you tightly filled it in small containers, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:07:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, since Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has witnessed this extraterrestrial\Nlife-form whose nature remains completely unknown to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.22,0:07:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit should be none other than this alien!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.23,0:07:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, this case will be\Nclassified in the "Top Secret X-File"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And kept in the dark depths of the Gunma Police HQ,\Nwhere it will never see the light of day again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.03,0:07:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, are you putting it away as unsolved?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.74,0:07:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention there's no such file.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.78,0:07:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did the alien have to kill the inn owner, Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't go along with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.37,0:07:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had always been using\Nbinoculars to watch over the river from this attic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.50,0:07:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must have seen them there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.71,0:07:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Swarms of kappa-looking aliens playing in the river water!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.93,0:07:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The aliens thought they'd been exposed and—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose it'd be easier to put this hack to sleep this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.65,0:07:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yamamura?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like Dad's "Sleeping Kogorou"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.11,0:08:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it perhaps the kappa's curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.28,0:08:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.20,0:08:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I said that name—\hkapow!—I\Nhad a sudden burst of inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.87,0:08:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.25,0:08:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even his non seguitur tie-ins are the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I... like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.13,0:08:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please call the remaining two suspects here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain to you the truth behind this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.22,0:08:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the name of the Gunma Police's First Division Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know who the culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:41.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Araiwa Kazuki (21)\NTatsuhiko's Classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:41.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Nohira Bousuke (45)\NReportage Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:40.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And you gathered all of us here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.11,0:08:43.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the murderer is among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.03,0:08:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't those suspicions have been cleared,\Ngiven that you've gone through our rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.33,0:08:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.21,0:08:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The point of consideration in this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.58,0:09:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the malodorous water from the reservoir ten kilometers\Ndownstream that drowned Numayama Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.05,0:09:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to drown him by putting that water\Nin the bucket, about one liter is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.18,0:09:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, the person who put that smelly water into some sort of\Ncontainer and brought at least a liter here is the culprit, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.60,0:09:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The colored ink bottles that Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nhad were all just about full of ink...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.69,0:09:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just now he used those inks to draw a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.40,0:09:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Araiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had two 500-milliliter plastic\Nbottles and a water pillow in his bag but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.49,0:09:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bottle with its seal broken still\Nhad half of its contents inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.33,0:09:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His water pillow was also flat upon entering the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.25,0:09:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for the two of them to bring a liter of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for Nohira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.63,0:09:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a large number of film canisters with\Nhim due to his job as a reportage writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.51,0:09:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But during the time of crime from 6 AM to 7 AM, he was conversing\Nwith his editor-in-charge over the phone and had a flawless alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.40,0:09:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that said, which of these three\N\Nare you pointing out as the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.02,0:09:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you find it odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aside from Nohira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who has an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.57,0:10:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Araiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, if there hadn't been someone who\Nwas familiar with the contents of their baggage prior to the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't have been able to escape suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we could've just assume that the water\Nwas brought in a paper carton or balloon...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.88,0:10:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that they destroyed the empty container after the crime\Nand flushed it down the toilet, feigning innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.38,0:10:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, we were able to discern the contents\Nof their baggage prior to the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.19,0:10:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.10,0:10:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You purposely lost your footing and fell in the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.53,0:10:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by saying you wanted to check your belongings,\Nyou spread everything out of your bag and revealed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all to set up this murder trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.75,0:10:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.80,0:11:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here with a letter\Nunder the suspicious name of Tatezato Mika...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And en route to the inn, he stopped Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ncar and managed to get a ride with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then said that he wanted to visit the gravesite of Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},\NBanzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s son, by the riverside before going to the inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.86,0:11:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All so he had an opportunity to fall into that river.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also dragged Araiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who happened to\Nbe visiting the grave, into falling with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.58,0:11:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that suspicion could be averted from his former student as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.92,0:11:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, did we tell you about the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.51,0:11:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.84,0:11:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That we came to this inn because a strange person called\Nus here whose name could be morphed into "kappa".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.10,0:11:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.68,0:11:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All sensei had were these small bottles of colored ink!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.44,0:12:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you get one liter of water from these?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are nine of the 60-milliliter bottles...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And sixteen of the 15-milliliter bottles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.53,0:12:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Including the 100-milliliter squirt bottle, they total 880 milliliters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.45,0:12:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you tightly fill all of the containers to the\Ntop, it would come out to about a liter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.88,0:12:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is enough to put in the bucket and drown someone with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was painting with those colored inks, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.76,0:12:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did use many colors...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.97,0:12:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the colors he didn't use perfectly match their labels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't use the squirt bottle, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, it's the empty squirt bottle that\Nwas rolling around on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, water is used to dilute the colored ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise the ink will be too thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was able to complete\Nthat faint picture without using any water.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.41,0:13:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the color ink stock solutions were only inside\Nthe dropper attached to the lid of the colored ink bottles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after the crime, they were diluted using tap water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using tap water?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sucked the ink into the dropper\Nbeforehand and emptied the bottle...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then filled the void with water from the\Nreservoir and drowned Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.40,0:13:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the crime, he poured in tap water to mix with\Nthe stock solutions in the dropper to provide color...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that it would seems to just be colored ink at first glance!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.45,0:13:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, the tips of the droppers were sealed\Nwith tape or something before the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To prevent the colored ink from mixing with the reservoir water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof, when he checked his baggage after falling in the\Nriver, Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't take his colored ink out of their cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had, it would've proven that inside them wasn't\Nvividly colored inks, but rather polluted reservoir water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.44,0:13:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he hadn't painted the picture, he might've gotten away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have much of a choice in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the crime, meticulously cleaning out so many bottles\Nin such a short amount of time is by no means possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some of it must remain there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.87,0:14:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remnants of the reservoir water inside the diluted colored inks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he purposely proposed using them to paint a picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to impress upon us that the contents of\Nthe bottles were, without a doubt, colored inks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if we ask the forensics to check the composition\Nof the inks, the results should soon be clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.23,0:14:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way sensei could be the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.60,0:14:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because sensei has never failed to visit the grave of Tatsuhiko,\Nwho was swept away by the river, for the past eleven years!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after the school was shut down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.66,0:14:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would sensei have to kill Tatsuhiko's father!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.58,0:14:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.95,0:14:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly because that man was Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I could never forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that man's fault that Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nwas swept away by the river and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same as if that man had killed him with his own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After school on the day before Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Nwas swept away by the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.98,0:15:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I happened to see him in the art room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that gloomy room, I saw a desperate Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} who\Nwas looking for paints that other students had left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought for sure he wanted to paint a\Npicture, so I gave him a new paint set, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few days after the river swept Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}\Naway, that man returned the paint set to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it looked as if none of the colors had been\Nused, I thought he hadn't painted any pictures...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I decided to keep them as they\Nwere, as a reminder of Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a few days ago I discovered something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:16:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The green paint alone had been replaced with another brand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why only the green paint?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.52,0:16:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dug up the grave to inspect the shoe that child had\Nbeen wearing when he was swept away by the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.91,0:16:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was convinced!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why there was green paint on the inside of the shoe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s whole body was painted\Ngreen on the day he was swept away by the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His whole body was green?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.51,0:16:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was ordered by his father to disguise\Nas a kappa and loiter around by the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.06,0:16:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to attract customers to his inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention in the cold December weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.90,0:16:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the witness statements of the kappa...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was likely Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, forced to be the kappa by that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.95,0:16:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man stripped the shoe off of Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s floating\Nbody in the reservoir and hid it close to his chest...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also replaced the green paint\Nbefore returning the actual set to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.96,0:17:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all to conceal the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.67,0:17:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why that man was using the\Nbinoculars to keep watch from the attic!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make sure that no one would dig\Nup the other shoe from the grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} decided for himself to dress up like the kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.06,0:17:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the sake of his father's inn, without even telling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.82,0:17:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if he ordered his son to do something like\Nthat, he'd normally just have him buy the paint!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.41,0:17:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he'd been seen by someone while scrounging around for\Npaint, it might have exposed that he was acting as the kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.50,0:17:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They even sell paint tubes individually, and it\Nwouldn't be strange for a child to buy paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.09,0:17:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did he take the shoe off of the corpse!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's for the late Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People might ridicule him once they find out\Nhe died while dressing up as the kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.18,0:17:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus it was a memento of his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:18:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, I think if it were such conclusive evidence, he would've\Ndisposed of it instead of walking around carrying it close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.81,0:18:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Araiwa-oniisan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.11,0:18:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} was telling the story of how she\Nsaw the kappa, you thought it was a ghost, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.03,0:18:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you knew that Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} had dressed up as the kappa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.46,0:18:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day Tatsuhiko got swept away by the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.09,0:18:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also by Tatsuhiko's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around that time, rumors had been spreading that the kappa was\Nsomeone in disguise since it never appeared when it was cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.02,0:18:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Tatsuhiko decided that he should do it on a cold day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.10,0:18:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him to stop since it had started to rain, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it was just drizzling and it would be all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that I should tell the guests at the inn to\Ncome and see the appearance of the kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.45,0:18:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as I was on my way to the inn, it really started pouring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.66,0:18:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I went back to tell him to stop, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.33,0:19:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuhiko's foot was already stuck between\Nthe riverbed rocks and couldn't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I called his dad over in a panic...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuhiko was already nowhere to be found!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.71,0:19:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you both started looking and ended up\Nfinding him downstream in that reservoir, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.64,0:19:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While taking off his green-stained shoe, Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.27,0:19:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to tell anyone about Tatsuhiko dressing up as the kappa...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.61,0:19:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if anyone was foolish enough to imitate him\Nand suffered the same fate, Tatsuhiko would be sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.57,0:19:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.45,0:19:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he was always watching over the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.95,0:19:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only to make sure no one got swept away by the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.04,0:19:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also to make sure no one would\Nfool around pretending to be a kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.21,0:19:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.88,0:19:46.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.21,0:19:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about the rumor of that guy prowling\Naround the area near the grave at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.72,0:19:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:20:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After kicking over the grave in front of his son's friends in order to\Nscare them away from the river, he secretly put it back together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.56,0:20:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it's just a grave made of stacked stones...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't change the fact it was an important\Nmonument made by his son's friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.25,0:20:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if in response to the wailing voice of\NTokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as he was taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.42,0:20:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our surroundings were thoroughly dyed\Nwith the sorrowful color of the sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I wept so hard yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.40,0:20:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realize it now I listen to the song
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.11,0:20:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to turn my feelings into words
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.78,0:21:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I see you, my heart is unable to find its voice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.45,0:21:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't treat me so gently
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.04,0:21:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Contrasting sceneries await us tomorrow, and I pray to God
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.63,0:21:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the last Time I want to remain by your side
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.97,0:21:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the last kiss, our hearts will connect even if we find ourselves apart
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.89,0:21:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the last Time Fulfill our dreams with me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.11,0:21:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's fly away on the last day - there's no need to worry, see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's fly away on the last day - there's no need to worry, see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.75,0:21:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed, Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.64,0:22:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess becoming an inspector's rubbed off on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.72,0:22:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea what he means...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.89,0:22:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since the case is solved, what do\Nyou say to getting a drink tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.98,0:22:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds good!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.90,0:22:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mystery of the kappa that I saw still hasn't been resolved!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.74,0:22:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still spouting such nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.12,0:22:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey you, knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.95,0:22:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you I really really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.75,0:22:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.96,0:22:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were so afraid that you just thought you saw it, understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.42,0:22:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.30,0:22:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talking to me as if I were a little kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.97,0:22:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're just a kid yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.60,0:22:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kappa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.14,0:22:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.73,0:22:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.10,0:22:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do something with your karate!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.23,0:22:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.61,0:22:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.53,0:22:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the kappa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.74,0:23:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, when I went to the grave to\Nsee if I could get some good pictures...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.04,0:23:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys suddenly showed up, I got surprised,\Nand ended up falling in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.70,0:23:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since your daughter kept going on about how it was the kappa...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.63,0:23:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought if I said the wrong thing I might be\Nmade into the culprit, so I stayed quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.40,0:23:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.85,0:23:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This painting shows the body as being thinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.72,0:23:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The abdomen juts out, and something\Nlike fur is coming from under the shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your body looked thin because you were drenched from\Nthe water, causing your clothes to stick to your body...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.49,0:23:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your abdomen was jutting out because\Nyou put something on there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.99,0:23:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, my films and other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.38,0:23:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.20,0:23:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this fur thing below the shell?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.25,0:23:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I play survival games occasionally, so I like\Nto put leaves on my body as camouflage...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.71,0:23:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.72,0:23:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what's solved is solved.
